<para>
  <classname>BasicDirect</classname> is a <link
  linkend="Section-Concepts-Mesh-Solvers-Matrix">matrix equation
  solver</link> used in <xref
  linkend="RegisteredClass-BasicSolverMode"/>.  It uses the <ulink
  role="external" url="http://www.netlib.org/lapack/">LAPACK</ulink>
  <ulink role="external"
  url="http://http://www.netlib.org/lapack/double/dgesv.f"><function>dgesv</function></ulink>
  function to solve equations via LU decomposition.  This requires the
  matrix to to converted from the sparse format used in &oof2; to a
  full represention, which uses a lot of memory.  It may be faster and
  more accurate for small matrices, however.
</para>


